g.text: Stage 1: Starting Life at UWPlan of Action: Pursue a degree in Computer ScienceAnalysis: While programming was fulfilling and interesting, it was cut and dry. I was hesitant to pursue a career that left little room to exercise creativity.Results: My application was rejected as I failed to qualify the criteria for CSE.Stage 2: Road to InformaticsPlan of Action: Explore new options that would combine my interests in technology and creativity.Process: INFO200 highlighted for me the possibility of using information technology and creative innovation to improve the world. In the final course project our group designed an app that facilitated the transfer of patient medical information among separate health-care entities.Results: I became confident that informatics would be a challenging, enjoyable, and fulfilling field to pursue. Its human-centered focus is one aspect that really draws me towards the field. I want to be able to create something that can help solve society’s problems and make a positive impact on the world.
